( 1 ) from
T. duellmani
in having modally seven pectoral-fin rays ( vs. modally eight), two pores in the lateral line ( vs. four), distal margin of the adpressed pelvic fin not reaching the anus ( vs. distal margin extending posteriorly beyond the anus), modally ten branchiostegal rays ( vs. six or seven), and modally 41 post-Weberian vertebrae ( vs. 33–36 ) (
